sql:
SELECT interaction_type
FROM drug_pairs
WHERE drug_pair_id = 1;

SELECT drug1, drug2, interaction_strength
FROM drug_pairs
ORDER BY interaction_strength DESC;

external_knowledge:
- Drug interactions refer to the effects that occur when two or more drugs are taken together; 
- Additivity refers to the combined effect of two drugs that equals the sum of their separate effects; 
- Synergy occurs when the combined effect of two drugs is greater than the sum of their separate effects; 
- Antagonism happens when the combined effect of two drugs is less than the sum of their separate effects.

- The threshold of 0.5 for the average effect strength is assumed to signify a moderate to strong interaction effect; 
- The timeframe of the first half of 2023 is chosen to analyze recent activities and effects of drug pairs; 
- Clinicians are considered the primary users for this analysis due to their professional expertise in drug interaction assessment.

